#### Given students' names along with the grade that they are in, create a roster for the school.

####   - "OK."  
#### - Get a list of all students enrolled in a grade

####   - "We've only got Jim just now."

####   Grades should sort as 1, 2, 3, etc., and students within a grade should be sorted alphabetically by name.

#include "grade_school.h"

namespace grade_school {

bool school::add(const std::string& name, int grade) {
    // Check all grades for existing student
    for (const auto& [g, students] : roster_) {
        if (students.count(name)) {
            return false;
        }
    }
    
    roster_[grade].insert(name);
    return true;
}

std::vector<std::string> school::roster() const {
    std::vector<std::string> result;
    for (const auto& [grade, students] : roster_) {
        result.insert(result.end(), students.begin(), students.end());
    }
    return result;
}

std::set<std::string> school::grade(int grade) const {
    if (auto it = roster_.find(grade); it != roster_.end()) {
        return it->second;
    }
    return {};
}

}  // namespace grade_school

The implementation:
- Uses `map<int, set<string>>` to maintain grades in order and names sorted
- `add()` checks all grades for duplicates before inserting
- `roster()` returns flattened vector of all students sorted by grade then name
- `grade()` returns empty set when no students in requested grade
- All returns are by value to prevent external modification
- Maintains const correctness for accessor methods
